  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCurrently `test_logger` is defined as a feature in `beacon_node/beacon_chain/Cargo.toml` and implemented in `beacon_node/beacon_chain/src/test_utils.rs`. I was working on [PR 2580](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/pull/2580) and needed to be able to see the logs and had to duplicate the code in `beacon_node/beacon_chain` so I could use it in `beacon_node/eth1`, which is not great.\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n```\r\n$ git log -1 --pretty=oneline\r\n8d2650fffd1be9070a8ebdbf01194755d274b379 (HEAD -> unstable, upstream/unstable, origin/unstable) Make local-testnet setup more discoverable (#2572)\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Present Behaviour\r\n\r\nCurrently `test_logger` only available in `beacon_node/beacon_chain` but other crates might find it useful.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behaviour\r\n\r\nMake `test_logger` available to all crates by having it defined under common. Currently there are a number of users of `null_logger` these should all be changed to use `test_logger` and the current behaviour will not change because if the `test_logger` feature is not specified `test_logger()` will return a `null_logger`.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nAdd `test_logger` under common.",
